# Magic Items

A sword is a tool. A *flaming* sword that never dulls and sheds light in darkness is a legend. Magic items transcend mundane equipment—they're the weapons that legends wield, the armor that heroes wear, the artifacts that campaigns revolve around.

Unlike consumables that disappear with use or mundane gear that anyone can purchase, magic items are permanent treasures that grow in significance throughout a campaign. The +1 longsword earned at third level becomes an heirloom. The ring of protection that saved you from death becomes irreplaceable. These items aren't just mechanical bonuses—they're story elements.

